40|$|Social media-led mass {{movements}} have dominated news headlines <b>in</b> recent times. <b>The</b> success {{stories of the}} Occupy movements, anti-globalisation demonstrations <b>in</b> <b>the</b> West, mass protests at Tahrir Square in Cairo and Taksim Square in Istanbul, demonstrations against <b>sexual</b> <b>harassment</b> <b>in</b> Delhi and <b>the</b> Shahbag Square uprising in Dhaka all underpin <b>the</b> fact that <b>in</b> both developed and developing societies, social media can potentially {{play an important role}} in organising large scale socio-political events. This ‘Behind the News’ article reflects on and analyses the recent ‘social-media-led’ political eruptions in two developing countries, Egypt and Bangladesh...|$|R
